  "description": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/korea-regulator-fines-google-street-view/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2012/10/google-street-view-car-parking-lot-masrur-odinaev.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n新年就一定要客客气气？韩国通信管理者可不这么认为。他们今天就一桩 2010 年的未授权数据搜集案向 Google 开出了 2.1 亿韩元罚单，要求后者为擅自使用不受保护 Wi-Fi 网络的行为付出代价（和之前在<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/04/22/google-street-view-fine-germany/\">德国</a>和<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2011/03/22/france-fines-google-100-000-for-street-view-privacy-violations/\">法国</a>的情况一样）。除了罚款外，Google 还被要求删除所有搜集到的数据，并且将相关细节公之于众。Google 这边目前还没有回应，或许正忙着和<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/google-and-samsung/\">三星</a>、<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/29/lenovo-nearing-3-billion-deal-for-motorola/\">联想</a>通电话拜年呢。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/01/30/korea-regulator-fines-google-street-view/\">Engadget</a>、<span class=\"via\"><a href=\"http://thenextweb.com/google/2014/01/30/korea-fines-google-196000-for-collecting-unauthorized-data-via-its-street-view-program/#%21tWzrb\" target=\"_blank\">TNW</a></span><br />\n引用来源：<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140128001166\" target=\"_blank\">Korea Herald</a></span></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/korea-regulator-fines-google-street-view/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20819212/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/korea-regulator-fines-google-street-view/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
